{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Cycling South Africa |abbrev = CSA |logo = Cycling_SA_Logo.jpg |logosize = 280px |sport = [[Cycling]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = {{Start date|}} |aff = [[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]] |affdate = |region = [[Confédération Africaine de Cyclisme|African Cycling Federation]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Cape Town]] |location = 3rd Floor, Skyscape Terraces, DJ Wood Way, [[Bellville, Western Cape|Bellville Business Park 7535]] |president = Zamuxolo "Yster" Xatasi (Acting) |secretary = Gregory van Heerden |url = www.cyclingsa.com |countryflag = South Africa |more = }}
'''Cycling South Africa''' or '''Cycling SA''' is the national [[sport governing body|governing body]] of [[bicycle racing|cycle racing]] in [[South Africa]]. Cycling SA is a member of the ''[[Confédération Africaine de Cyclisme]]'' and the ''[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]'' (UCI).<ref>[http://www.uci.ch/inside-uci/organisation/national-feds/federation/south-africa-rsa/ UCI website September 2017]</ref> It is affiliated to the [[South African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee]] (SASCOC),<ref>[http://www.sascoc.co.za/cycling-south-africa/ SASCOC website September 2017]</ref> as well as the [[Sport and Recreation South Africa|Department of Sport and Recreation SA]]. Cycling South Africa regulates the five major disciplines within the sport, both amateur and professional, which include: road cycling, mountain biking, BMX biking, track cycling and para-cycling.
Cycling South Africa’s “2020 Vision” strategy, to cater for both the elite cyclist as well as the everyday two- and three-wheel lovers, contributes to the organisation being a dynamic, successful and highly respected governing body of cycling, at both national and international level. Cycling South Africa is committed to transformation and development of the sport and making it accessible to all via its development programmes.
