{{Infobox football club |clubname = Ulaanbaatar City F.C. |image = Ulaanbaatar_City_FC_Logo.png |image_size= 200px |fullname = Ulaanbaatar City Football Club |founded = 19 March 2016<ref name="Г.Дашням">{{cite web|title=Г.Дашням: Хөрөнгө, менежмент дээр л тулгуурлаж хөгжсөний хүчинд хөлбөмбөг дэлхийн хаан спорт болсон биш гэж үү?|url=http://ekhsurvalj.mn/news/view/1900|publisher=ekhsurvalj.mn|accessdate=14 October 2017|language=Mongolian}}</ref> |ground = [[G-Mobile Arena]] |capacity = 3,000 |owner = MT Group, GMobile Co.,LTD |chrtitle = President |chairman = Dashnyam Ganzorig |manager = [[Steve Nicholls]] |league = [[Mongolian Premier League]] |season = [[2018 Mongolian Premier League|2018]] |position = '''6th''' }}
'''Ulaanbaatar City''' is a [[Association football|football]] club from [[Ulaanbaatar]], [[Mongolia]]. They currently play in the [[Mongolian Premier League]], the highest level of football in Mongolia and made their debut appearance in the [[2016 Mongolian Premier League|2016 season]]. Since January 2017 the team has been coached by Spaniard [[Manuel Retamero Fraile]].<ref name="Manuel Retamero">{{cite web|last1=Lahuerta-Efe|first1=Juan Jose|title=Manuel Retamero, el pucelano errante|url=http://www.elnortedecastilla.es/deportes/futbol/201701/04/manuel-retamero-pucelano-errante-20170104130123.html|publisher=elnortedecastilla.es|accessdate=15 October 2017|language=Spanish}}</ref>
==History== The club was founded on 19 March 2016 with club owner, the IT Group, purchasing the [[Mongolia Premier League]] license of [[Khangarid FC]] which was subsequently dissolved.<ref name="Г.Дашням"/> The IT Group paid 15 million [[Mongolian tögrög|MNT]] for the license.<ref name="Г.Дашням: Би хөлбөмбөгийн">{{cite web|title=Г.Дашням: Би хөлбөмбөгийн багийн эзэн болохыг багаасаа мөрөөдсөн|url=http://ikon.mn/n/157m|publisher=Ikon.mn|accessdate=24 November 2017|language=Mongolian}}</ref>
==Stadium== Through the 2017 season, Ulaanbaatar City FC shared the [[MFF Football Centre]] as a home ground. Ground was broken for the construction of the team's own [[G-Mobile Arena]] in late summer of 2017 with the anticipated completion being in the third quarter of 2018. The stadium will be the fifth venue in the league along with the MFF Centre, [[Erdenet Stadium]], the [[National Sports Stadium (Mongolia)|National Sports Stadium]], and [[Erchim Stadium]].<ref name="New G-Mobile Arena Under Construction">{{cite web|last1=Grimm|first1=Justin|title=Ulaanbaatar City FC's New G-Mobile Arena Under Construction|url=http://www.mongolianfootball.com/single-post/2017/10/04/Ulaanbaatar-City-FCs-New-G-Mobile-Arena-Under-Construction|publisher=Mongolian Football Central|accessdate=14 October 2017}}</ref>
